chair.description: This photo captures a lot of the things Felix enjoys doing lately: he likes kneeling (better than regular sitting); he likes to climb under chairs; he likes babbling loudly; and he likes pushing toys against things, like a table or daddy's face.
chair.title: Chair

drawer.description: When Felix gets tired of sitting in his high chair, but mom and dad want to buy a little more time at the dinner table, some quiet lap-and-drawer time is a family favorite.
drawer.title: Drawer

first-step.description: We told you about it last week, but now we have the photo to prove it: Felix is taking steps! It is still a slow and unstable way to go, but Felix is very proud just the same.
first-step.title: First Step

jack-o-lantern1.description: We got some pumpkins and carved them into Jack-O-Lanterns. This is Jacques.
jack-o-lantern1.title: Jack O Lantern 1

party-beer1.description: Felix didn't get to stay for the Halloween party (he spent the night over at Rebecca's, his baby-sitter), but he helped clean up. Here, he checks out the left-over beer.
party-beer1.title: Party Beer 1

description:
The weather is getting more wintery, and Felix caught his first cold. He has a runny nose, and he is feeling cranky and more tired than usual. Still, he is diligently practicing taking steps.

On Saturday, we had a big Halloween bash. Here are the photos.
title: October 27
